This paper discusses attacks against machine learning systems, which are typically studied in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer security (cs.CR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the transferability of attacks across different models, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and software engineering (cs.SE) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CR, and cs.AI, followed by cs.CV and cs.SE.
